<!--
  User-facing string resources (default / English).

  Conventions for contributors and future strings:
  - Key names are <screen_or_area>_<element>, lower_snake_case.
  - Wrap every format argument in <xliff:g> so translators neither reorder
    nor translate it. A dropped or mangled %1$s crashes the app at runtime,
    which is why MissingTranslation + the StringFormat lint checks are a
    hard CI gate (see app/build.gradle.kts).
  - Count-dependent text uses <plurals> + pluralStringResource, never a
    hand-rolled if (n == 1) - plural rules differ by language.
  - Machine / diagnostic strings (capture-log lines, hex, JSON keys, BLE
    protocol, log tags, navigation route ids) stay hardcoded in Kotlin and
    are never translated.

  Translating the app: see CONTRIBUTING.md. Copy this file to
  values-<lang>/strings.xml and translate only the text between the tags.
-->
